}}
[[File:Caves3.jpg|thumb|190px|<center>The first English edition (1892)</center>]]
This work has been translated into English two times. The first translation appeared in 1892 in London{{sfn|Britannica|1911}} but was not complete. It was done by Vera Johnston, Blavatsky's niece.{{sfn|Cranston|1993|p=57}} A new 1975 translation by [[Boris de Zirkoff]] (also Blavatsky's relative) is now available in author's ''Collected Writings'' series.{{sfn|Blavatsky|1975}} Subsequently, the book was repeatedly reprinted, in English, Russian and Spanish.{{sfn|Formats and editions}}{{refn|group=note|The first Spanish edition was a translation from English published by [[Mario Roso de Luna]].{{sfn|Fernández}}}}{{refn|group=note|"24 editions published between 1892 and 2013 in 3 languages and held by 64 WorldCat member libraries worldwide."{{sfn|WorldCat Identities}}}}

