{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} {{More footnotes|date=September 2013}} '''Pedro Marieluz Garcés''' (or '''Peter Marielux''') (born in 1780 in [[Tarma]]/Peru, died on 23 September 1825 in [[Callao]]/Peru) <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.religiososcamilosperu.org/300/pdf/04.pdf |title=Religiosos Camilos : Necrologio del Convento de la Buenamuerte (1709 - 2009) |publisher=Reliosocamilosperu.org |accessdate=2013-09-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203095648/http://www.religiososcamilosperu.org/300/pdf/04.pdf |archivedate=3 February 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> was a Roman [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[priest]] who died as a [[martyr]] of the [[Seal of the Confessional and the Catholic Church|Seal of the Confessional]].
As a young man, Pedro Marieluz Garcés entered the order of the [[Camillians]] and was [[Holy orders|ordained]] a priest in 1805.
Later he became a military chaplain with the troops of the Spanish Royal Governor, [[José Ramón Rodil y Campillo|Ramón Rodil]]. During the siege of the fortress Real Felipe in the city of [[Callao]] after the [[Battle of Ayacucho]], there was a conspiracy made against Rodil by some of the Royal soldiers. The plot was discovered and Rodil sentenced the conspirators to death. They were allowed to [[Confession (religion)#Roman Catholicism|confess]] to Father Marieluz before being shot. After the execution of the plotters, Rodil is said to have doubted whether he had convicted all members of the plot and, thinking that the executed ones would have revealed everything in confession to Father Marieluz, he tried to force the confessor to disclose to him what he had heard under the holy seal by threatening him to be shot likewise, if he would not obey. But Father Marieluz remained steadfast and thus died a [[martyr]] in the evening of 23 September 1825, as his legend tells us.
==Sources== *[https://archive.org/stream/holinesschurch00kempuoft#page/n379/mode/2up "Father Peter Marielux" in The Holiness of the Church in the nineteenth Century] *[http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article111088701 "A Martyr Priest", Article in the Freeman's Journal, Thursday, 23 May 1912, page 36] *[http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article57841572 "A Martyr Priest", Article in the Klimore Free Press, 11 July 1912] *[http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article116765690 "The Story of Father Marielux. Martyr of Sacramental Seal" in the Freeman's Journal, Thursday, 17 December 1925, page 40]
